Đoàn Thống Lĩnh is a Junior Backend Developer with 0 years of commercial experience, demonstrating a strong foundation in backend system design and development through significant academic and personal projects. Their core expertise lies in architecting scalable solutions using Microservices and MVC, implementing Message Queue systems with RabbitMQ and Kafka, and applying a wide array of design patterns including Singleton, Strategy, Template, Command, State, Builder, Observer, Flyweight, Decorator, and Factory for clean, optimized, and hand-crafted architecture systems. They are proficient in developing RESTful APIs and integrating WebSocket for real-time functionalities. Notable project experience includes developing a cross-platform library management system with user authentication, comprehensive catalog management, and admin controls, and a multi-platform e-commerce application (Android, Web, Windows) featuring advanced product catalogs, shopping cart, order management with tracking, real-time reviews, and an analytical admin dashboard. Additionally, they engineered an English vocabulary learning application leveraging Firebase, advanced design patterns, and community features, showcasing strong problem-solving, logical thinking, system analysis, and energy optimization skills.
Technically, Đoàn is proficient across multiple programming languages including Dart, Python, C, C#, and Java, with hands-on experience in frameworks such as Flutter, Node.js, and Android development. Their database management skills encompass MongoDB, MySQL, and SQL Server. For cloud and DevOps, they are experienced with Firebase, and proficiently use Git, GitHub, and GitLab for version control and collaborative workflows. Holding an intermediate English proficiency (APTIS Level B1 CEFR) and a Bachelor of Software Engineering (in progress) with a GPA of 8.64, Đoàn is also certified in Agile Development & Scrum Framework, emphasizing their dedication to clean code principles, comprehensive documentation, effective team collaboration, and communication within an Agile/Scrum methodology.